======================================================================
H-SPECTRUM DENSITY ANALYSIS
======================================================================

Spectrum at n=7: 77 values, max=189
Odd integers in [1,189]: 95
Density at n=7: 77/95 = 0.8105

Gaps in [1,189] at n=7 (18 gaps):
  [7, 21, 63, 107, 119, 149, 161, 163, 165, 167, 169, 173, 177, 179, 181, 183, 185, 187]

Permanent gaps (proved all n): [7, 21]
Gaps at n=7 that may fill later: [63, 107, 119, 149, 161, 163, 165, 167, 169, 173, 177, 179, 181, 183, 185, 187]

Gap analysis:
  7 = 7*1
  21 = 7*3
  63 = 7*9 -- ACHIEVED at n=8 (not permanent)
  107 -- no obvious pattern
  119 = 7*17
  149 -- prime
  161-169 (block): 7*23, 163(prime), 165=3*5*11, 167(prime), 169=13^2
  173 -- prime
  177-187 (block): top end near max=189

Gaps divisible by 7: [7, 21, 63, 119, 161]
Gaps NOT divisible by 7: [107, 149, 163, 165, 167, 169, 173, 177, 179, 181, 183, 185, 187]

Density d(N) = #{H in spectrum <= N} / #{odd <= N}:
  N=   50: 23/25 = 0.9200
  N=  100: 47/50 = 0.9400
  N=  150: 69/75 = 0.9200
  N=  200: 82/100 = 0.8200
  N=  300: 132/150 = 0.8800
  N=  500: 232/250 = 0.9280
  N= 1000: 482/500 = 0.9640

Asymptotic: as H -> infinity, density(H) -> 1 - 0/infinity = 1
The TWO permanent gaps {7,21} have zero density: |{7,21}|/#{odd<=N} -> 0

